iDocker is a container management software for Linux. Each container is		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifunctionally similar to an OpenVZ VPS, allowing isolation of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iapplications on a server. This isolation enables different versions of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe same software or conflicting applications to run on the same		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iserver. For example, MySQL 5.7, MySQL 5.6, and MariaDB 10.1 can run		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isimultaneously in three separate Docker containers on one server.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iHowever, Docker surpasses OpenVZ in its more flexible Linux kernel		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iversion requirements. OpenVZ kernels remain stuck at 2.6.32 (stable)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand 3.10 (development), while Docker runs on any Linux kernel above		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3.10. My server currently uses Linux kernel 4.9 (for BBR support),		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwhich clearly cannot run OpenVZ but works perfectly with Docker.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAnother advantage of Docker is its comprehensive image repository and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iautomation tools. With OpenVZ, I had to log into each VPS individually		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ito configure networks, run `apt-get` , and perform regular backups.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iWith Docker, I can directly use pre-built software images (no need for `apt-get` )		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand map data folders directly to the host machine (eliminating		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iseparate backups).		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iDocker also provides Docker Compose, which allows configuring multiple		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
icontainers via a configuration file for rapid deployment and removal.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
