i## Creating an Image from apt-get Installed Software		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iPHP7.0-FPM is more complex. The official PHP-FPM image uses unusual		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
icompilation flags and configuration paths that differ from my DotDeb		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iinstallation. To avoid issues, I created a custom Docker image.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iBuilding Docker images requires only basic bash knowledge. Create a		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
inew folder, then add a Dockerfile with the following structure: (Comments		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iafter # are mine)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  FROM debian:jessie # Base image		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  MAINTAINER Lan Tian "lantian@lantian.pub" # Optional author info		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ADD somefile.txt /somefile.txt # Add local file to image		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  RUN apt-get update # Execute command during build		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  EXPOSE 80 # Expose port to other containers		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ENTRYPOINT ["php-fpm7.0"] # Startup command (container stops when this exits)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor this image, I need to: add DotDeb repository, run `apt-get` , add		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
icustom configs, expose ports, and set the startup command. My		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iDockerfile:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  FROM debian:jessie		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  MAINTAINER Lan Tian "lantian@lantian.pub"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ADD dotdeb.gpg /dotdeb.gpg		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  RUN echo "deb http://packages.dotdeb.org jessie all" >> /etc/apt/sources.list \		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      && echo "deb-src http://packages.dotdeb.org jessie all" >> /etc/apt/sources.list \		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      && apt-key add /dotdeb.gpg \		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      && apt-get update \		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      && apt-get install -y php7.0-fpm php7.0-bz2 php7.0-curl php7.0-gd php7.0-json php7.0-mbstring php7.0-mcrypt php7.0-memcached php7.0-mysql php7.0-redis php7.0-sqlite3 php7.0-xml php7.0-xmlrpc php7.0-zip \		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      && apt-get clean		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ADD www.conf /etc/php/7.0/fpm/pool.d/www.conf		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
